p>Public Service Vehicles = Buses and Coaches (including minibuses with 9-16 seats)</p></td><td><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>2. Hybrid vehicles may be under-recorded for Public Service Vehicles and Heavy Goods Vehicles: other includes gas and electric</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong></strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-05T14:19:52.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425475/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425475/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Motor Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) passenger vehicles, (b) vans, (c) public service vehicles and (d) heavy goods vehicles are licensed; and how many vehicles in each such category (i) use petrol, (ii) use diesel and (iii) are hybrid.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","14349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425476","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Department for Transport has not made any assessments on the effect of the cost of acquiring a Certificate of Professional Competence (CPC) on access to such Certificates for young people.</p><br /><p>In order to allow newly qualified drivers to gain experience, the department allows those who have passed the theory test (module one) and practical driving test (module three) to enrol on an approved National Vocational Training (NVT) programme and defer taking the Driver CPC theory and practical tests. This allows a driver to work professionally for up to 12 months whilst working towards a Driver CPC qualification.</p><br /> <br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-05T13:12:07.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425476/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425476/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Driving: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of the cost of acquiring a Certificate in Professional Competence on access to such certificates for young people.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","14308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425477","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Department for Transport has not made any assessment on the economic effect of a potential driver shortage specific to the Humber area.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-05T13:15:08.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425477/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425477/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Driving: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect on businesses in the Humber area of the shortage of Certificate of Professional Competence qualified drivers.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","14309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425478","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Department for Transport has not made an estimate on the economic effect of a potential driver shortage. It is aware of extensive reports about pressures on wages, the recruitment of drivers from outside the UK and delayed deliveries.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-05T14:08:07.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425478/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425478/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Driving: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the economic cost of the shortage of Certificate of Professional Competence qualified drivers.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","14310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425479","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>The majority of public funding for local bus services is via block grant provided to local authorities in England from the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p><br /><p>In 2014-15 my Department provided funding of around £250 million in Bus Service Operators Grant, of which over £40 million per year is now paid direct to authorities to help support bus services. This figure excludes some £93 million a year previously paid to bus operators for running bus services under franchise to Transport for London (TfL) in London, which is now incorporated into the general grant paid to TfL and the Greater London Authority.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-10T11:44:50.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425479/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425479/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Bus Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the reduction was in his Department's support for bus funding in England in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","14281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425480","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Department does not centrally record this information.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-10T11:39:17.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425480/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425480/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Department for Transport: Stationery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the value of stationery that has been (a) lost and (b) stolen from his Department in each of the last five fiscal years; and what the cost was of replacing such stationery.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","14376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425481","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>In terms of rail, Ministers and Department for Transport officials regularly discuss the regulation of Network Rail and the railways with the Office of Rail and Road (ORR).</p><br /><p>In 2015 ORR has carried out consultations on both its railways and Highways Monitoring enforcement policies. DfT responded to both consultations. I understand ORR will publish revised policies in due course.</p><br /><p>In relation to monitoring Highways England, the Infrastructure Act 2015 conferred the monitoring function on ORR and Highways England was appointed as a Strategic Highways Company on 1 April 2015.</p><br /><p>The ORR Highways Monitor has been provided with statutory guidance to develop its enforcement plan. This statutory guidance was jointly issued with HM Treasury on 20 March 2015 and can be found on the gov.uk website.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-11-10T11:23:31.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425481/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425481/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Office of Rail and Road","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Office of Road and Rail (ORR) monitoring framework; and what guidance he has provided to the ORR as it develops its enforcement plan.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425482","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The government is tripling the capital investment in the Strategic Road Network. Highways England have been given responsibility for delivery of the Road Investment Strategy and operation of the network.</p><br /><p>A four year term contract was tendered competitively by Highways England to a consortium consisting of CH2M Hill, Mace and PwC (CMP) in early July 2015 to help provide additional support to improve their capability and available resources to deliver an increasingly demanding and complex programme.</p><br /><p>This has no impact on the role, responsibilities and requirements of Highways England.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14425 ; 14446","2015-11-05T16:21:11.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425482/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425482/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Highways England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with Highways England on the appointment of a programme management partner; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425483","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The government is tripling the capital investment in the Strategic Road Network. Highways England have been given responsibility for delivery of the Road Investment Strategy and operation of the network.</p><br /><p>A four year term contract was tendered competitively by Highways England to a consortium consisting of CH2M Hill, Mace and PwC (CMP) in early July 2015 to help provide additional support to improve their capability and available resources to deliver an increasingly demanding and complex programme.</p><br /><p>This has no impact on the role, responsibilities and requirements of Highways England.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14426 ; 14446","2015-11-05T16:21:11.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425483/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425483/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Roads","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the respective roles of (a) Highways England and (b) its proposed programme management partner in the delivery of the Road Investment Strategy Programme.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425484","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Secretary of State for Transport’s Private Office does not subscribe to any publications.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-05T12:48:24.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425484/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425484/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-02","Department for Transport: Subscriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what publications his private office subscribes to.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","14418"
