"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425103","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-04","<p>Under the Welfare of Racing Greyhounds Regulations 2010, there is no statutory requirement on any greyhound organisation or individual track to report any figures to Defra. The Regulations have now been in force for five years and Defra is currently undertaking a review of their effectiveness. The review is looking at the requirement on tracks to collect injury statistics and how they are then used; and the traceability of greyhounds after they have left the sport. Defra intends to consult on the initial findings of the review.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","14227 ; 14228","2015-11-04T16:31:07.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425103/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425103/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-30","Greyhounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the number of greyhounds which retired from racing in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","14233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425104","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-05","<p>We are due to publish our 25 year plan for British food and farming early in 2016.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-11-05T10:56:16.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425104/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425104/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-30","Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she expects work on a long-term strategy for UK food and farming to conclude; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","14216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425105","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-05","<p>Food supply is one of the UK’s critical national infrastructures and Defra produces an annual sector resilience plan as lead Government Department.</p><br /><p>The UK food sector has a highly effective and resilient food supply chain, owing to the size, geographic diversity and competitive nature of the industry. The resilience of the sector has been demonstrated by the response to potentially disruptive challenges in recent years, although it is dependent on other critical services such as fuel, energy, transport and communications. The Government and industry work together closely to identify and mitigate risks and ensure the continued resilience of food supply.</p><br /><p>The Government is developing a 25 year food and farming plan to further grow our food and farming industry. We want to export more and produce more for the domestic market. We aim to improve productivity and profitability through greater efficiency, the deployment of new technology and by building on the strong international reputation of British food at home and abroad.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-11-05T11:23:10.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425105/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425105/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-30","Food Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of the most significant key risks to the UK's food security; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","14217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425106","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-06","<p>Statistics on the proportion of UK crops used for biofuel production are only available from 2012. Figures for 2012 and 2013 are given in the attached table. 2014 data is to be published on GOV.UK this December.</p><br />","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-11-06T10:18:50.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425106/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425106/answer","881 - 14218  - UK biofuel production.pdf","881 - 14218  - UK biofuel production.pdf","Biofuel production","Biofuel production","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425106/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-30","Agriculture: Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much and what proportion of UK agricultural output was used in the production of biofuels in each year from 2000-01 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","14218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425107","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>We strongly condemn the attack against the civilian residents of Camp Liberty in Iraq on Thursday 29 October. Officials from our Embassy in Baghdad raised the attack with the Iraqi Prime Minister’s Office on 30 October and made clear the importance of an urgent and comprehensive investigation into the incident and ensuring that all those responsible are brought to justice.</p><p>In all of our engagement with the Government of Iraq on this issue, including at Ministerial level and in our statements, we have emphasised the importance of the Iraqi Government doing everything possible to ensure the safety of the residents of Camp Liberty.</p><p>It is the responsibility of the Government of Iraq to protect Camp Liberty. We have therefore not raised the attack with the Iranian authorities.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-11-04T14:35:59.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425107/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425107/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425107/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-30","Iraq: Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the (a) Iraqi and (b) Iranian authorities on the missile attack on Camp Liberty, Baghdad, on 29 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","14159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425108","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>We intend to update the House about the main findings of the Muslim Brotherhood Review shortly. We have been clear from the outset that the purpose of the Review is to get a better understanding of what the Muslim Brotherhood stands for, how they intend to achieve their aims and what that means for the United Kingdom.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-11-04T14:33:21.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425108/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425108/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-30","Muslim Brotherhood Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he plans to publish the report of the review into the Muslim Brotherhood; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","14208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425109","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<p>From the data collected it is not possible to identify how much was spent specifically on treating patients with age-related macular degeneration.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-09T16:21:33.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425109/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425109/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425109/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Macular Degeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much the NHS spent on treating age-related macular degeneration in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","14193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425110","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<br /><p>Prior to hospital discharge every patient will have a discharge assessment which will look at their ongoing healthcare needs and in light of that an individual care plan will be established.</p><br /><p>These plans are formed in line with each individual hospital’s discharge policy, which will vary.</p><br /> <br /> <br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-09T16:14:36.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425110/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425110/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425110/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Eyesight: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what arrangements are in place for assessing a patient's eye health on discharge from hospital.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","14194"
