"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425120","Department of Health","false","2015-11-04","<p>The information is not available in the format requested. The information in the attached table shows episodes of leave starting on a Friday, Saturday and Sunday for each London mental health trust, between 1 January 2015 to July 2015.</p><br /><p>The attached table is provided by the Health and Social Care Information Centre.</p><br /> <br /> <br /> <br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-04T17:03:09.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425120/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425120/answer","Episodes of leave- London mental health trust January-July 2015.xlsx","Episodes of leave- London mental health trust January-July 2015.xlsx","Weekend leave- London mental health trusts 2015","Weekend leave- London mental health trusts 2015","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425120/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Mental Health Services: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on how many occasions patients were granted weekend leave in each mental health hospital in London in each month since 1 January 2015.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","14185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425121","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Department has made no estimate of the number of people likely to have age-related macular degeneration in 2050.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-09T16:09:14.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425121/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425121/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Macular Degeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of people likely to have age-related macular degeneration in 2050.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","14226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425122","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<p>We have no plans to do so.</p><br /><p>The UK Government is committed to tackling antimicrobial resistance. The UK Antimicrobial Resistance Strategy, published in September 2013, proposed strong, cross-government action to manage this problem. The UK strategy recognises the central part diagnostics, like C-reactive protein tests, play in getting the right antibiotic drug to the right patient at the right time. A working group is actively looking at what can be done to improve diagnostic services.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-11-09T16:11:41.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425122/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425122/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Respiratory System: Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will assess the (a) potential effect on the number of antibiotic and (b) potential change in annual prescription and dispensing costs prescriptions of using C-reactive protein testing for patients presenting with respiratory tract infections in primary care.","false","Biography information for Maggie Throup","Erewash","Maggie Throup","14222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425123","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>The UK Clinical Health Research Analysis (2015) shows that, in 2014, the combined government spend on medical research into eye disease, development and function was £15.1m, or 1.2% of public funding on health research. The report is available at <a href="http://www.hrcsonline.net/pages/uk-health-research-analysis-2014" target="_blank">http://www.hrcsonline.net/pages/uk-health-research-analysis-2014</a> (page 95).</p><p>The Research Councils account for approximately half of this expenditure and support research in response to proposals from the academic community. They welcome high quality applications for support into any aspect of human health which are judged in open competition with other demands on funding. Awards are made according to their scientific quality and importance to human health.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-09T16:27:05.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425123/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425123/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-30","Eyesight: Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the proportion of medical research spending which is spent on eye disease.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","14200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425124","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the trends in the cost of treating sight loss and eye health problems.</p><br /><p>However, the table below shows expenditure for ‘problems of vision’ for primary care trusts (PCTs) for 2011-12 and 2012-13 and for clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) for 2013-14.</p><br /><p>Expenditure on problems of vision, 2011-12 to 2013-14</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Commissioner</p></td><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Total £ billion</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>PCTs</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>2.26</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>PCTs</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2.30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>CCGs</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>1.6<sup>1</sup></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Note: </em></p><p><sup>1</sup> This figure does not include services directly commissioned by NHS England, such as primary eye care services. NHS England is currently reviewing expenditure data on their directly commissioned services.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","14202","2015-11-09T16:18:40.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425124/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425124/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425124/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-30","Eyesight: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of trends in the costs of treating sight loss and eye health problems.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","14201"
