"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425147","Home Office","false","2015-11-10","<p>Figures on the numbers of search warrants and surveillance authorisations subject to judicial review are not held centrally.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2015-11-10T17:00:35.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425147/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425147/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425147/answer/previousversion/27749","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-30","Judicial Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) search and (b) surveillance warrants issued by a judge have been subject to judicial review in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","14186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425148","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-04","<p>The three EU countries with the largest number of foreign national offenders in prison are; Poland 951, Ireland 783 and Romania 629 as of 30th September 2015 last published figures.</p><p>The EU Prisoner Transfer Agreement is beginning to take effect. Poland has a derogation until the end of December 2016 from the agreement to allow time to improve their prisons.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-11-04T09:40:15.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425148/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425148/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-30","Prisoners: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which three EU countries have the largest number of foreign nationals in UK prisons; and how many such prisoners there are from each of those countries.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","14264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425149","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-04","<p>The decision to release Roberts was made by the independent Parole Board based on the risk presented by him. It is not appropriate for Ministers to interfere with decisions of the Parole Board to release an offender, or to seek disclosure of the Board’s reasoning.</p><br /><p>Since Roberts’ release, the Government has changed the law so that the sentencing starting point is a whole life order for anyone who is over age 21 and convicted of the murder of a police or prison officer.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-11-04T16:03:29.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425149/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425149/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-30","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will request that the Parole Board publish the basis on which it took the decision to release Harry Roberts from prison in October 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","14246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425150","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-07","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer given to PQ 13074 on 7 December 2015.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-12-07T16:12:58.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425150/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425150/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-30","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when his Department plans to answer Question 13074, on Ministry of Justice: Public Expenditure, tabled by the hon. Member for Hammersmith on 22 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","14261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425151","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-16","<p>I refer the Honourable member to the answer given to question 12150 on 06 November 2015.</p><br /><p>This can be found at: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-15/12150/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-15/12150/</a></p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-11-16T11:27:51.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425151/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425151/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-30","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to answer Question 12150, on HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Procurement, tabled by the hon. Member for Hammersmith on 15 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","14262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425152","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>We are the first Government ever to deliver a National Living Wage. Every employer in the country will pay the National Living Wage, including all Government contractors, from April 2016.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-05T13:17:25.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425152/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425152/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425152/answer/previousversion/27855","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-30","Government Departments: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make it his policy that no Department be permitted to (a) employ staff at wages below the living wage and (b) sign a contract with contractors who pay their staff less than the living wage.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","14179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425153","Scotland Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>Transparency information for the period July 2014-March 2015 was published on 15 October as the information was ready for publication.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-11-04T15:24:50.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425153/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425153/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-10-30","Scotland Office: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, for what reason his Department's three most recently published quarterly returns were all published on the same day.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","14206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425154","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p>The Government recognises the value that passengers attach to direct services in preference to having to change trains.</p><br /><p>The specification for the new TransPennine Express franchise, which starts in April 2016, requires the future franchisee to continue to operate through services between Hull and Manchester. The Government’s response to the consultation on the new Northern and TransPennine Express franchises, published in February, made clear that decisions on the post-electrification service pattern for Hull would be taken during the life of the new franchises. In the meantime, the specifications for the new franchises will provide Hull passengers with an improved weekday evening service back from Manchester, a full hourly all-day service to/from York, and additional trains to/from Scarborough.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-04T17:12:36.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425154/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425154/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it is his policy to require the new TransPennine Express franchise to include direct Hull, Leeds and Manchester services at the same frequency as is currently provided.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","14205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425155","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p>Network Rail has identified<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> that crowding issues on the West Coast Main Line (WCML) mean that, whilst there is the potential to run a small number of additional services, the WCML will be effectively full by 2024. The lack of capacity will become even more acute beyond 2024 as demand continues to grow. This will negatively affect both freight and passenger services. The western leg of HS2 Phase Two alleviates these capacity constraints in the Warrington area.</p><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><p><sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> Network Rail: West Coast Main Line Route Utilisation Strategy</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-04T15:20:05.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425155/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425155/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the contribution that the Hoo Green to Bamfurlong spur of High Speed 2 is likely to make to reducing capacity constraints on the West Coast Main Line; and what account that estimate takes of (a) rail freight and (b) passenger services to Warrington Bank Quay and elsewhere.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","14180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425156","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-06","<p><strong></strong>The Department for Transport has not made any such estimates. There are a number of behavioural, educational and technological interventions that have the potential to help improve young driver safety. We need better evidence about what works best, so we’re working with insurance companies to see how we can assess the impact of telematics products on young driver safety.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-06T11:10:40.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425156/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425156/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of how many (a) drivers and (b) drivers under 25 were using black box technology in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425157","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p>The Department considers that franchisees are normally best placed to procure the rolling stock that they require to deliver the necessary levels of service and capacity. We expect the competition for the next East Midlands long-term franchise to deliver those improvements to the rolling stock that are required.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-11-04T16:47:57.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425157/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425157/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Midland Main Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has for replacement of the HST 125 trains on the Midland mainline.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","14265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425158","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Department commissioned four scientific studies into cabin air in 2007. All studies commissioned by the Department were submitted to the Committee on Toxicity of Chemicals in Food, Consumer Products and the Environment for consideration in 2012. The Committee published a position paper on cabin air in December 2013, which can be accessed in full electronically at: <a href="http://cot.food.gov.uk/sites/default/files/cot/cotpospapcabin.pdf" target="_blank">http://cot.food.gov.uk/sites/default/files/cot/cotpospapcabin.pdf</a>.</p><br /><p>In addition to the Department’s studies, the European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) has launched a preliminary in-flight cabin air measurement campaign in spring 2015, the results of which are expected in autumn 2016.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-09T14:23:06.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425158/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425158/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Aviation: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of emissions containing organo-phosphates produced by aircraft engines on airline and airport staff and passengers.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425159","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p>As with all competitions, after running a public consultation to help specify services, we have published the Invitation To Tender which sets out the minimum service specifications for the next East Anglia franchise. This asks bidders to set out detailed proposals on what improvements for passengers they will deliver. This approach allowsbidders the flexibility to design the best way of delivering or exceeding the specifications.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-11-04T14:58:39.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425159/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425159/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","East Anglia Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to increase the frequency of train services to north-east Essex along the Great Eastern Main Line.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","14220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425160","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-06","<p>The provision of bus services that require subsidy is a matter for individual English local authorities, in the light of their other spending priorities. Latest figures (2013-14) show that £318m a year was spent by local authorities (outside London) doing so.</p><br /><p>My Department also provides around £40m of Bus Service Operators Grant (BSOG) funding directly to English local authorities to help deliver bus services. This central funding has been ring-fenced until 2016-17.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-06T11:29:44.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425160/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425160/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Bus Services: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of how many subsidised bus routes have been withdrawn since 2010.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","14242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425161","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p>Funding for Bikeability is currently confirmed until the end of March 2016. We will take a decision on future funding for the Bikeability programme beyond March 2016 following the outcome of the Spending Review.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-04T16:15:12.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425161/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425161/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Cycling: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to fund Bikeability beyond 2015.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","14243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425162","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-06","<p>All future budgets, including those for sustainable transport, remain subject to Spending Review negotiations. Further information will be made available after the outcome of the Spending Review is announced on 25 November.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-06T11:15:10.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425162/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425162/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-30","Transport: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department's plans are for long-term local sustainable transport funding.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","14241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425163","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-04","<p>The Department is following the procedures for the assurance and support of major projects outlined in ‘HM Treasury the Major Project approval and assurance guidance’ introduced from April 2011. More details can be found in the link below.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/179763/major_projects_approvals_assurance_guidance.PDF.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/179763/major_projects_approvals_assurance_guidance.PDF.pdf</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-04T17:07:35.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425163/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425163/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-30","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reason the universal credit programme was subject to Project Assessment Reviews instead of Gateway Reviews.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425164","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-11-04T10:02:33.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425164/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425164/answer","PQ 14266.pdf","PQ 14266.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Rate of Employment","UKSA Letter to Member - Rate of Employment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425164/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-30","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress the Government has made on increasing the rate of employment in (a) Northamptonshire and (b) England since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","14266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424776","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-23","<br /><p>Total employment in the UK grew by a larger amount than in any other EU member state during this period, according to Eurostat data. Since quarter one 2012 to quarter two 2015 the employment level in UK has increased by 1.6m. This compares to approximately 826,000 in France, 1.3m in Germany and 101,400 in Spain.</p><br />",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-11-23T11:53:22.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424776/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424776/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Job Creation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how the United Kingdom compares with other European Union member states in terms of the number of jobs created since the start of 2012.","false","Biography information for Baroness Eaton",,"Baroness Eaton","HL3119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424777","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>The Companion to the Standing Orders distinguishes between amendments to approval motions whose effect is to withhold the agreement of the House to an affirmative instrument, and amendments or motions that do not prevent approval of the instrument (Companion to the Standing Orders, Para. 10.14). The terms “fatal” and “non-fatal” do not appear.</p><p /> <p>The amendments in the name of Baroness Meacher and Baroness Hollis of Heigham passed by the House on 26 October withheld the House’s agreement to the Tax Credits (Income Thresholds and Determination of Rates) Regulations 2015.</p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2015-11-12T15:08:57.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424777/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424777/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Statutory Instruments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they define (1) a fatal, and (2) a non-fatal, motion, or amendment to a motion, relating to a statutory instrument.","false","Biography information for Lord Grocott",,"Lord Grocott","HL3120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424778","Leader of the House of Lords","false","2015-11-12","<p>Including all those peers whose introduction or retirement has been advertised in <em>House of Lords Business</em>, and assuming no other changes to the membership of the House, as of 19 January 2016 there will be 249 members on the Conservative benches, 212 members on the Labour benches, and 112 members on the Liberal Democrat benches. This means that there will be 75 more peers on the benches of the largest two opposition parties than on the Government benches.</p><p><strong><br></strong>That will be 29 more peers than at the end of the 2009-10 session, when there were only 46 more peers on the benches of the largest two opposition parties than on the Government benches.</p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2015-11-12T15:09:18.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424778/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424778/answer",,,,,"92",,"Leader of the House of Lords","2015-10-29","House of Lords Composition","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by the Lord Privy Seal on 26 October (HL2541), whether they will publish the latest figures on the number of members of each party in the House, and the ratio of government to opposition members, including all those peers whose introduction has been scheduled.","false","Biography information for Lord Grocott",,"Lord Grocott","HL3121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424779","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-11","<p>Data on the amount of civil plutonium in the UK are published each year by the Office for Nuclear Regulation. As of 31 December 2014 there was <strong>126.3 tonnes.</strong> <strong>Detailed information</strong> can be found at <a href="http://www.onr.org.uk/safeguards/civilplut14.htm" target="_blank">http://www.onr.org.uk/safeguards/civilplut14.htm</a>.</p><br /><p>Data on the amount of civilian plutonium as of 31 December 2015 will be published in the spring 2016.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-11-11T13:02:01.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424779/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424779/answer","Annual civil plutonium and uranium figures as of 31 December 2014.pdf","Annual civil plutonium and uranium figures as of 31 December 2014.pdf","Annual civil plutonium & uranium figs as 31.12.14","Annual civil plutonium & uranium figs as 31.12.14","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424779/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-10-29","Plutonium","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the size of the present stockpile of plutonium held in the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL3122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424780","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-11","<p>The Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) are in the process of submitting advice to support DECC in its considerations. This, together with other sources of information and evidence, will enable DECC to consider options for the way forward. A decision is expected to be made by ministers on how to proceed during 2015/16. Only when the Government is confident that its preferred option could be implemented safely and securely, in way that is affordable, deliverable, and offers value for money, will it be in a position to proceed.</p><br />",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-11-11T13:02:27.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424780/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424780/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-10-29","Plutonium","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the current status of the plutonium disposal programme.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL3123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424781","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-11","<p>We expect the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) to submit a report to DECC to support us in our considerations on the policy options in due course. Informed by the advice from NDA, ministers will then make an assessment of the options, and decide on the appropriate next steps. Only when the Government is confident that its preferred option could be implemented safely and securely, in way that is affordable, deliverable, and offers value for money, will it be in a position to proceed.</p><br />",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-11-11T13:03:00.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424781/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424781/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-10-29","Plutonium","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the security implications of the various options for disposal of plutonium.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL3124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424782","Home Office","false","2015-11-11","<p>Advice and guidance on protective security and preparedness to terrorist threats is provided by specialist Counter-Terrorism Security Advisors (CTSAs) who operate in every police region.</p><p>The number of CTSAs in post in England and Wales in April 2010 was 191. The number in post in England and Wales in April 2015 was 146 (this figure includes 4 Counter Terrorism Awareness Advisers dedicated towards the provision of CT awareness advice).</p><p>Government aims to have 171 staff in post by the end of 2016/17 (145 CTSAs and 26 CTAAs). These planned changes to resource are for the effective and efficient delivery of future advice and guidance, whilst ensuring they maintain their fundamental role as part of wider police capabilities to safeguard the security of the public.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-11-11T16:55:25.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424782/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424782/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-29","Police: Counter-terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government  how many police Counter Terrorism Security Advisers were employed in England and Wales in (1) April 2010, and (2) April 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL3125"
