"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424815","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-11","<p>The Review of UK product recalls chaired by Lynn Faulds Wood is due to be published soon.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-11-11T16:19:27.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424815/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424815/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Recall of Unsafe Products Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they anticipate publication of the results of the review of the United Kingdom's system for the recall of unsafe products chaired by Lynn Faulds Wood.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL3158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424816","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-06","<p>The decision whether or not to publish any responses is a matter for the Chief Coroner.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-11-06T12:35:38.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424816/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424816/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424816/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-29","Carbon Monoxide: Poisoning","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will publish their response to the report of the coroner David Hinchcliff, <i>Inquests Touching the deaths of Christianne Shepherd and Robert Shepherd</i><i>(Deceased)</i>, published on 18 September.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL3159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424817","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-11","<p>All licence applications are rigorously assessed on a case by case basis against the Consolidated EU and National Export Licensing Criteria. A licence would not be granted if to do so would be a breach of the Criteria.</p>",,"Lord Maude of Horsham",,"2015-11-11T13:01:16.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424817/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424817/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424817/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Yemen: Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their policy regarding the licensing of arms, including British-made military aeroplanes, to the Saudi Arabian-led coalition which is conducting airstrikes in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424818","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-09","<p>The people of Taiz are in urgent need of humanitarian supplies. The city continues to experience intense fighting, which is making it extremely difficult for aid agencies to deliver humanitarian assistance. There are reports that efforts to access the city and provide relief have been consistently blocked by the Houthis over the past month.</p><br /><p>The UK continues to call on all parties to facilitate rapid, safe and unhindered access to all people in need in Yemen. We will continue to monitor the situation closely and support UN and NGO partners' efforts to deliver humanitarian assistance to Taiz city.</p><br /><p>On 27 September 2015, the Seretary of State announced an additional £20million for humanitarian assistance to Yemen, bringing our overall contribution for 2015-16 to £75million and making the UK the 4th largest bilateral donor to Yemen crisis</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-11-09T17:54:31.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424818/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424818/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424818/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-10-29","Yemen: Armed Conflict","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the response to conditions in the southern Yemen city of Taiz.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424819","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-13","<p>UK Official Development Assistance (ODA) channelled through non-governmental organisations is set out in the table below. DFID is currently conducting the Civil Society Partnership Review, which is considering future funding arrangements.</p><p>2014 data will be published on the DFID website as National Statistics on Thursday 3<sup>rd</sup> December 2015.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Channel Code Description</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013 ODA (£ millions)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>% of Total UK ODA</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NGO (where country base is undefined)</p></td><td><p>£150,895</p></td><td><p>1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Internationally-based (non-UK) NGO*</p></td><td><p>£362,696</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK-based NGO*</p></td><td><p>£662,307</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Developing country-based NGO</p></td><td><p>£178,313</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>*Many international and UK-based NGOs have significant local developing country footprints.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-11-13T09:06:03.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424819/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424819/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424819/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-10-29","International Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the proportion of aid funding which is channelled to large international agencies compared to that channelled to local non-governmental organisations.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424820","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-05","<p>Whilst we do not have a contractual obligation to have a duty of care for the staff of international aid agencies that are funded by DFID, all DFID funding is subject to DFID’s Due Diligence procedures which assess an organisation’s governance and control structure and those of their downstream partners.</p><br />",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-11-05T16:48:39.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424820/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424820/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424820/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-10-29","International Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of international aid agencies' efforts to support and protect their staff from sexual abuse.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424821","Home Office","false","2015-11-11","<p>Those migrants who seek asylum will have their claims considered by the Cypriot authorities on behalf of the Sovereign Base Authorities (SBA). There is no obligation to allow those recognised as refugees to take up residence in the UK.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-11-11T16:54:54.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424821/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424821/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424821/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-29","Refugees: Syria","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to the recent statement of the UNHCR that, under a 2003 United Kingdom–Cyprus memorandum, the United Kingdom is responsible for resettling Syrian refugees who arrive at a United Kingdom military base in Cyprus.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424837","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<br /><p>The budget for the Employment Agency Standards inspectorate for 2011-12 was £776,643.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-09T15:51:32.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424837/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424837/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the annual budget for the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate was in 2011-12.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","14006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424838","Home Office","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Home Office have previously published data on the numbers of non-human primates imported and used for scientific research in PQs 222873 (05 Feb 2015), 182703 (20 Jan 2014), 80687 (22 Nov 2011) and 76262 (25 October 2011). The numbers of non-human primates imported into the UK for scientific research were: 2,071 in 2010; 1,771 in 2011; and, 1,557 in 2012. This data was gathered from information supplied by project licence holders when requesting permission to import.</p><p>On 1 January 2013, the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986 was amended to transpose European Directive 2010/63/EU on the protection of animals used for scientific purposes. The amended legislation has no requirement to request prior permission to import non-human primates acquired from overseas breeding centres. Therefore, the Home Office does not hold the information requested for 2013 and 2014. The published Annual Statistics of Scientific Procedures on Living Animals in Great Britain provide information on the sources of non-human primates used in experimental procedures for 2013 and 2014.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-11-09T17:38:53.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424838/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424838/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424838/answer/previousversion/27569","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-29","Primates: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many primates were imported into the UK for scientific research purposes in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","14011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424839","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-03","<p>Through the Waste and Resources Action Programme (WRAP), the Government is working with food manufacturers and retailers to meet targets to reduce food and packaging waste from the grocery supply chain under the Courtauld Commitment.</p><br /><p>Signatories reported a reduction of 7.4% in supply chain waste between 2009 and 2012 under Courtauld 2. Interim results for Courtauld 3 show signatories reported a further 3.2% reduction by 2014 against the overall target of a 3% reduction by the end of 2015.</p><br /><p>WRAP is currently brokering a new agreement, Courtauld 2025, which will build on this progress and is expected to start in 2016.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-11-03T12:00:25.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424839/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424839/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-29","Food: Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to encourage retailers to reduce the amount of food waste they produce; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","14012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424840","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Government is working through the Aerospace Growth Partnership and the Aerospace Technology Institute (ATI) to promote UK growth by supporting industry to develop technologies for future aircraft.These will need to meet demanding environmental and societal requirements, and the ATI supports the targets for reducing noise and emissions set out by the Advisory Council for Aviation Research and Innovation in Europe (ACARE).These targets include reductions by 2050 in fuel burn of 75%, a reduction of Nitrogen Oxides (NOx) emissions of 90% and a reduction in perceived noise of 65% based on a year 2000 baseline.</p><p>To date, over 100 ATI projects, worth a total of over £1bn, have been approved.The majority of these are focused on technologies for more efficient and environmentally friendly aircraft.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-09T14:53:52.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424840/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424840/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Aviation: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of progress by the Aerospace Technology Institute on reaching its goal of reducing fuel emissions by 20 per cent over the next 20 years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","14031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424841","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-04","<p>The World Trade Organisation (WTO) Agreement on Trade Facilitation, agreed at the Bali Ministerial in December 2013, is expected to significantly reduce the costs of cross-border trade, including between developing countries.The Agreement was opened for acceptance by WTO Members in November 2014 and, to date, 51 WTO Members, including all EU Member States, have ratified.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-04T11:40:54.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424841/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424841/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","World Economy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the 2013 Lough Erne G8 Leaders' Communiqué, published on 18 June 2013, what progress has been made on implementing the commitments in paragraph 9 of that document; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","14089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424842","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-05","<p>Statistics on the timeliness of responses to Freedom of Information requests are published by Government (Table 4 of annual reports). They are available here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p><p>These statistics provide the number of requests which were answered within the 20 day deadline, the number of requests where additional time was required for the consideration of public interest, and the number of late responses.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-05T15:22:52.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424842/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424842/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what average time his Department took to respond to Freedom of Information requests in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","14057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424843","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-04","<br /><p>The Government published the first part of a two-part consultation on the statutory Pubs Code on 29 October 2015 at the GOV.UK website.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-04T17:33:14.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424843/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424843/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent progress he has made on publishing a statutory code for pub companies; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","14115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424844","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-04","<p>Decisions on the size of stake retained in the Green Investment Bank will be taken on the basis of what achieves best value for money for the taxpayer.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-04T17:35:52.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424844/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424844/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what he plans for the size of the stake which the Government will retain in the Green Investment Bank to be after that bank's privatisation.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424845","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-04","<br /><p>The Government allocated up to £3.8 billion of funds to Green Investment Bank (GIB) for investment in the period to March 2016. To date, GIB has made commitments totalling £2.1billion. Government will fund these and any further commitments GIB enters into during the current year to March 2016.</p><br /><p>GIB’s funding needs for the year 2016/17 are being considered as part of the current spending review and the outcome will be announced later in the year.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-04T17:31:36.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424845/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424845/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans his Department has for the £1.8 billion of uncommitted Green Investment Bank funds following privatisation of that bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424846","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-05","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills has engaged with the European Commission and our European partners. He has spoken with a number of European Commissioners in Brussels; Commissioner Cecilia Malmstrom (Trade), Commissioner Elzbieta Bienkowska (Internal Market) and Vice President Jyrki Katainen (Jobs and Competitiveness), and stressed the importance of this issue. He has had positive talks with the Competition Commissioner Margrethe Vestager on progressing the approval of the UK’s Energy Intensive Industries compensation scheme.</p><br /><p>I raised the issue with Matthias Machnig, State Secretary for the German Ministry of Economic Affairs and Energy. In addition, the Secretary of State hasraised the issue with his EU counterparts, including those in Luxembourg, France, Italy and Spain. ​Hecalled for an urgent EU Council meeting on steel, and I am pleased that the Luxembourg Presidency has scheduled a Competitiveness Council on9 November specifically to discuss the EU steel industry.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-05T17:18:51.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424846/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424846/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Iron and Steel: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he, his ministers and his officials have had with the European Commission on the situation in the steel industry.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424847","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-30","<p>Green investment is what the Green Investment Bank (GIB) does and is where its value lies. It is clear from preliminary feedback that potential investors are interested in GIB precisely because of its unique green specialism and its existing forward business plan and pipeline of green projects. Investors will have sound commercial reasons to maintain GIB’s green focus and continue operating in accordance with its clearly stated green principles and highly transparent and robust green reporting practices.</p><p>As a key part of any sale discussions, potential investors will be asked to confirm their commitment to these values and to set out how they propose to protect them. We envisage this would involve new shareholders agreeing to:</p><ul><li>ensure GIB continues to invest in a way that achieves a positive green impact; and</li><li>maintain GIB’s existing standards for reporting on its green investment performance as well as continue providing for independent assurance of this.</li></ul><p>It is important to understand Government could not impose binding conditions on future owners of GIB to act in a particular way while also securing our key objective of removing state control over GIB so it can be reclassified to the private sector.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-30T14:16:21.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424847/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424847/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what ability the Government plans to retain to ensure that the Green Investment Bank operates according to its original purposes after that body's privatisation.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424848","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>The government has put paying down our debt while investing in infrastructure at the heart of our long term economic plan. The sale proceeds will therefore help us deliver on both those objectives.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-09T15:00:01.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424848/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424848/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans the Government has for potential financial proceeds from the privatisation of the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424849","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>Proceeds will depend on the size of stake sold and the outcome of negotiations with investors about the value of the company. We will need to be satisfied any transaction represents value for money for the taxpayer.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-09T14:55:50.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424849/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424849/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much the Government intends to raise from privatisation of the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","14107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424850","Home Office","false","2015-11-13","<p>Individuals are not appointed to the Community Engagement Forum. Attendance at the meetings will rotate to allow ministers to hear directly from a wide range of individuals and groups taking a leading role in challenging extremism as well as sharing thier expertise and initiatives on building stronger community relationships.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-11-13T15:00:44.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424850/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424850/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424850/answer/previousversion/27571","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-29","Community Engagement Forum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, who has been appointed to the Community Engagement Forum; what criteria were used to make those appointments; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","14141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424851","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>Information relating to the proceedings of recent Cabinet Committee meetings is not disclosed as to do so could harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion. Cabinet Committee minutes and other papers, which are not subject to national security or other restrictions, will be released to The National Archives after 20 years once the transition from the 30 to the 20-year rule has been complete. A detailed list of the Cabinet Committees, including their membership and remit, can be found on Gov.uk.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2015-11-03T13:30:36.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424851/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424851/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Cabinet Committees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 29 October 2015 to Question 13434, on Cabinet Committees: Airports, under what circumstances (a) full minutes, (b) dates of and (c) other information about such meetings would be published.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424852","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>For security reasons we do not comment on specific details of unsuccessful cyber security attacks.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-04T10:07:16.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424852/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424852/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Electronic Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what attacks have been made against the Government Gateway system to date.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","14047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424853","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>In total 103 Local Authorities in England are receiving additional funding to help target their remaining carry forward entries. Almost £570,000 of funding was allocated directly to 53 English authorities where carry forward entries accounted for over 5%, as a proportion of their registers, in May 2015. 59 Local Authorities in England, including 9 which had already received a direct allocation, successfully submitted bids for additional funding, sharing just over £450,000.</p><p>The attached table sets out all 103 English authoritieswhich are receiving additional funding directly and those whhich submitted successful bids along with the total amount they are receiving.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-11-03T17:15:56.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424853/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424853/answer","CO-DC00-PRN01_Emman Chowdhury_4208_001.pdf","CO-DC00-PRN01_Emman Chowdhury_4208_001.pdf","Attachment for Member","Attachment for Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424853/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Electoral Register: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Written Statement of 16 July 2015 by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary, Cabinet Office, HCWS 127, on individual electoral registration, how much of the funding referred to in that statement has been allocated to each electoral registration office in England.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","14037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424854","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>To date the security reports on the Government Gateway system do not show a cyber-security breach.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","13981","2015-11-03T13:31:44.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424854/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424854/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Electronic Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what information his Department holds on the potential sale of information stolen during the cyber-security breach of the Government Gateway system.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","14038"
