"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424868","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-11","<p>We have made available over £500 million to local authorities and the voluntary sector to tackle homelessness and since 2010 this has helped local authorities to prevent 935,800 households from becoming homeless.</p><p>Since 2010, local councils have had more flexibility over how they spend the money they receive from central government.</p><p>The allocation of Homeless Prevention Grant has developed over many years to take account of different kinds of pressures, including rough sleeping and statutory homelessness. We supported the establishment of the National Practitioner Support Service’s ‘Gold Standard’ programme to help improve the effectiveness of local authority homelessness prevention services.</p><p>Decisions on funding beyond 2015/2016 will be subject to the forthcoming spending review.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","14097 ; 14098","2015-11-11T16:44:49.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424868/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424868/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-29","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department has made to ensure that the homelessness prevention grant is being used effectively.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","14099"
