"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424983","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Criminal Cases Review Commission is independent, and it would not be appropriate for Ministers or officials to intervene in individual cases.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-11-03T17:05:53.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424983/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424983/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-29","James Thompson","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will make representations to the Criminal Cases Review Commission on reviewing the case of James Thompson.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","14066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424984","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-06","<p>13 temporary staff were employed through the Brook Street Agency and a Crown Commercial Services Recruitment framework and were selected by the Legal Aid Agency and interviewed by permanent members of staff to ensure their suitability. These individuals made up 19% of the overall assessment team. In addition contracts were entered into with legal practices to provide additional resource.</p><br /><p>The key criteria for employment were analytical skills and the ability to conduct a qualitative assessment. A legal or procurement background was considered an advantage but not essential, given that they would be supervised by permanent staff from the Legal Aid Agency.</p><br /><p>The procurement was undertaken in line with the Public Contract Regulations and applicant organisations were required to pass a number of stages of assessment in order to be considered suitable to hold a duty provider contract. The criteria against which organisations were assessed is set out in the Information For Applicants which govern this procurement process.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","14001 ; 14002 ; 14003 ; 14005","2015-11-06T10:46:47.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424984/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424984/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-29","Legal Aid Agency: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what training was provided to the people who assessed bids for legal aid duty solicitor contracts in administering and assessing such contracts.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","14004"
