"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424989","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government has asked Lord Strathclyde to lead a review to examine how to secure the decisive role of the elected House of Commons in relation to (i) its primacy on financial matters; and (ii) secondary legislation. Lord Strathclyde will be supported by a panel of experts and further details will be announced in due course.</p><br />","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-11-03T17:08:16.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424989/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424989/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-29","Committees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the daily rate or fee will be for members of the proposed review committee on securing the decisive role of the House of Commons on financial matters and secondary legislation.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","14022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424990","Leader of the House","false","2015-11-06","<p>The sitting days of the House are kept under review and I would welcome representations on the issue the hon. Gentleman raises, either from individual Members or political parties.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2015-11-06T09:35:22.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424990/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424990/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-10-29","Times of Sittings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, if he will consult political parties on proposals to change the sitting days of the House during party conferences.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","14085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424991","Prime Minister","false","2015-11-03","<p>I have raised the issues facing the steel industry with my counterparts, including most recently with the Prime Minister of Luxembourg, which currently holds the EU Presidency.</p><br /><p>The Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills is also engaged with the European Commission and our European partners. He has spoken with a number of European Commissioners in Brussels; Commissioner Cecilia Malmstrom (Trade), Commissioner Elsbieta Bienkowska (Internal Market) and Vice President Jyrki Katainen (Jobs and Competitiveness), and stressed the importance of this issue. He has had positive talks with the Competition Commissioner Margrethe Vestager on progressing the approval of the UK’s Energy Intensive Industries compensation scheme.</p><br /><p>In addition, the Secretary of State has raised the issue with his EU counterparts, including those in Luxembourg, France, Italy and Spain. He called for an urgent EU Council meeting on steel, and I am pleased that the Luxembourg Presidency has scheduled a Competitiveness Council on 9 November specifically to discuss the EU steel industry.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-11-03T16:43:01.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424991/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424991/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-29","Iron and Steel: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when he last discussed the issue of state aid for the UK steel industry with (a) the President of the European Commission, (b) the Presidency of the European Council and (c) other EU member state governments.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","14024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424992","Prime Minister","false","2015-11-03","<p>Information about the first meeting of the Community Engagement Forum can be found on the gov.uk website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-11-03T16:43:57.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424992/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424992/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-29","National Community Forum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will publish the minutes of the Prime Minister's Community Forum meeting on 13 October 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","14142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424993","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-06","<p>It is too early to estimate the efficiency savings gained from the reorganisation of Highways England which was created on 1 April 2015. The Department for Transport published the Roads Reform Programme Evaluation Framework in March. This includes a clear expectation that the evaluation will be carried out over a number of years, given the number of the changes made. In addition the Office of Rail and Road, will continue to monitor the performance of Highways England including efficiencies. The table below shows the capital expenditure of Highways England, with resource spend and the depreciation of road asset value.</p><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p>Resource (excl.depreciation)(£m)</p></td><td><p>Resource Depreciation (£m)</p></td><td><p>Capital (£m)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>1,000</p></td><td><p>866</p></td><td><p>1,823</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>1,012</p></td><td><p>929</p></td><td><p>1,425</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>1,038</p></td><td><p>914</p></td><td><p>1,034</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>1,145</p></td><td><p>870</p></td><td><p>1,288</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>1,214</p></td><td><p>775</p></td><td><p>1,654</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-06T10:53:13.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424993/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424993/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Highways Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the efficiency savings his Department has gained from the reorganisation of the Highways Agency to Highways England; and what the budget of that body was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424994","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Department sponsors the Disabled Persons Transport Advisory Committee (DPTAC). DPTAC has a Chair and 12 members with a range of impairments. It advises the government on transport legislation, regulations and guidance and on the transport needs of disabled people, ensuring disabled people have the same access to transport as everyone else.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-03T11:44:37.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424994/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424994/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Public Transport: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to involve disabled people in the design of better access to public transport.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424995","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>Bids are currently being evaluated for the TransPennine Express (TPE) franchise and we expect to announce the winning bidder and its rolling stock plans by the end of the year. When the detailed plans for TransPennine electrification are confirmed, the Department will work with the TPE franchisee to ensure that the necessary rolling stock is put into place; this is expected to take place during the franchise term.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-03T16:59:26.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424995/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424995/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects new rolling stock to be introduced on the forthcoming Transpennine Express franchise; and whether that rolling stock is planned to be diesel or electric powered.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","14008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424996","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>Analysis presented in the HS2 Economic Case published in October 2013 calculated that the benefit cost ratio (BCR) of HS2 is valued at 2.3 for the full Y-network, including wider economic impacts. Therefore, over £2 worth of benefits are expected for every £1 spent which represents high value for money.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-03T15:25:13.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424996/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424996/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent estimate his Department has made of the forecast return on investment from the High Speed 2 project; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","14007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424997","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>No. The death of Mr O’Malley was not a maritime accident as defined in law, and is considered to be a health and safety at work incident. It therefore falls outside the responsibilities of the Department for Transport and its Danish counterpart.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-03T15:19:24.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424997/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424997/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Stephen O'Malley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make representations to his Danish counterpart on reopening the inquest into the death of commercial driver Stephen O'Malley in 2012.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","14010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424998","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government recognises the value that passengers attach to direct services in preference to having to change trains.</p><br /><p>The specification for the new TransPennine Express franchise, which starts in April 2016, requires the future franchisee to continue to operate through services between Hull and Manchester. The Government’s response to the consultation on the new Northern and TransPennine Express franchises, published in February, made clear that decisions on the post-electrification service pattern for Hull would be taken during the life of the new franchises. In the meantime, the specifications for the new franchises will provide Hull passengers with an improved weekday evening service back from Manchester, a full hourly all-day service to/from York, and additional trains to/from Scarborough.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-03T17:03:46.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424998/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424998/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to ensure that direct rail services between Hull, Leeds and Manchester continue regardless of which parts of that route are electrified.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","14013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424999","Home Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>We will type approve Mobile Evidential Breath Test Instruments (MEBTIs) as soon as possible. Type approval is a complex process and relies on the submission by manufacturers of instruments which then perform satisfactorily during testing. The Home Office has no control over these factors.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-11-03T15:58:31.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424999/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424999/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-29","Driving under Influence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans for portable evidential breath-test machines to be made available for use by the police to tackle drink driving.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","14033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425000","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-04","<p><strong></strong></p><p>An airport company may prohibit a person from entering the Airport under provisions in their byelaws.</p><br /><p>As this is a matter for the airport concerned the Department does not hold details of any person so prohibited.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-04T16:10:06.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425000/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425000/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Aviation: Passengers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what provisions are in place to enable airports to ban passengers from their premises; under what circumstances such provisions may be used; and how many passengers were banned from (a) Leeds Bradford International, (b) Belfast International, (c) East Midlands, (d) Edinburgh, (e) Glasgow International, (f) Manchester, (g) Newcastle International, (h) London Gatwick, (i) London Luton, (j) London Stansted and (k) London Heathrow Airport in each year from 2010 to 2015 to date.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","13987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425001","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-18","<p>All workers subject to the Working Time Regulations, including aircraft maintenance engineers, are entitled to a number of protections. These include entitlement to annual leave and rest breaks, a limit on weekly working hours, and restrictions on night work.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-18T12:59:39.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425001/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425001/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-29","Aviation: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on the application of working time regulations to aircraft maintenance engineers.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","13986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425002","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government has not set road safety targets for local authorities or the police, and is not considering reinstating them. We do not believe that further persuasion is needed on the importance of road safety through “Whitehall knows best” diktats. However, local authorities and the police are free to set their own targets if they find this useful.</p><br /><p>The Conservative Manifesto 2015 had a commitment to reduce the number of cyclists and other road users killed or injured on our roads every year. We are working closely with road safety groups to consider what more can be done and we believe that every death is a tragedy and is one too many.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","13985","2015-11-03T15:38:58.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425002/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425002/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish a national road safety strategy.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","13984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425003","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government has not set road safety targets for local authorities or the police, and is not considering reinstating them. We do not believe that further persuasion is needed on the importance of road safety through “Whitehall knows best” diktats. However, local authorities and the police are free to set their own targets if they find this useful.</p><br /><p>The Conservative Manifesto 2015 had a commitment to reduce the number of cyclists and other road users killed or injured on our roads every year. We are working closely with road safety groups to consider what more can be done and we believe that every death is a tragedy and is one too many.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","13984","2015-11-03T15:38:59.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425003/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425003/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-29","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will set road casualty reduction targets.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","13985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425004","Wales Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>As Secretary of State I meet regularly with many non-party political organisations to discuss a range of issues, including the draft Wales Bill. These include business organisations, representatives of the legal profession, academics and representatives of Welsh civil society.</p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb","14079 ; 14080","2015-11-03T13:02:55.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425004/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425004/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-10-29","Devolution: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, which non-party political organisations he has worked with in developing the proposed Wales Bill.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","14017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425005","Wales Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>As Secretary of State I meet regularly with many non-party political organisations to discuss a range of issues, including the draft Wales Bill. These include business organisations, representatives of the legal profession, academics and representatives of Welsh civil society.</p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb","14017 ; 14079","2015-11-03T13:02:55.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425005/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425005/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-10-29","Devolution: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, with which non-party political organisations he has met to discuss the proposed Wales Bill since March 2015.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","14080"
