"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425007","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Department has been working closely with its new provider, the Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA) to develop and test new processes for obtaining further evidence as part of the Work Capability Assessment. An initial test of these new processes should start by the end of the year.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-05T16:07:29.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425007/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425007/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress his Department has made in piloting reasonable adjustments to the work capability assessment for people with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425008","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>Despite routine re-assessments are currently suspended to focus on new claims, we have made an exception for deteriorating conditions where a repeat assessment can be requested. As a consequence no changes have been made to the re-referral periods for people in the Support Group.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-03T16:52:40.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425008/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425008/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress his Department has made in extending reassessment periods for claimants in the employment and support allowance support group (a) generally and (b) who have degenerative brain conditions.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","14120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425009","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>The information as requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","14049 ; 14055","2015-11-03T15:27:21.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425009/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425009/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425009/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Employment and Support Allowance: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many appeals by claimants in the work related activity group of employment and support allowance have resulted in subsequent placement in the support group of employment and support allowance in each quarter since 2013.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425010","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>The information as requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","14048 ; 14055","2015-11-03T15:27:21.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425010/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425010/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Work Capability Assessment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of appeals against fit for work decisions since January 2013 have involved people whose primary medical condition is a mental health condition.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425011","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-05","<p>The level of information requested is not available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-05T16:03:07.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425011/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425011/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Work Capability Assessment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average cost to his Department is of an appeal against a fit for work decision.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425012","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>Jobcentre Work Coaches undertake outreach work every day in local communities, and have recently been helping people with back-to-work support and advice at the Lalley Centre in Manchester. Early feedback has been very positive. We will reflect on this and see if there is potential for extending engagement where there is local need and Jobcentre Plus are invited to do so.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","14114","2015-11-03T11:15:18.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425012/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425012/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Jobcentre Plus: Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what criteria he will use to decide whether to extend the placement of jobcentre advisers in food banks beyond the current pilot.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425013","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>We are always striving to improve the Work Capability Assessment and especially the claimant experience. To this end we have implemented, or are implementing, over 100 recommendations identified following five independent reviews. All assessments are carried out by health professionals trained in Disability Assessment Medicine and receive guidance for medical conditions which include fluctuating conditions such as Multiple Sclerosis.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-03T17:07:44.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425013/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425013/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Work Capability Assessment: Multiple Sclerosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the Multiple Sclerosis Society's recent findings that almost half of the people with multiple sclerosis surveyed who had had a work capability assessment declared that it had caused their condition to deteriorate or relapse.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","14138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425014","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>We have made it clear that when attending a face-to-face consultation, claimants can bring someone with them in order to support them or help them manage any anxiety they may feel. In some cases assessment providers will also carry out consultations in claimants’ homes.</p><p>Assessments for PIP are carried out by qualified health professionals who have broad training in assessing the impacts of a variety of disabilities, including fluctuating conditions such as Multiple Sclerosis. Before claimants are invited for a face-to-face consultation, all of the evidence held is reviewed and if, at that stage, a decision can be made on the paper evidence alone, then claimants will not be required to attend a face-to-face consultation.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-03T15:18:59.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425014/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425014/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Personal Independence Payment: Multiple Sclerosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the Multiple Sclerosis Society's recent findings that 36 per cent of people with multiple sclerosis surveyed who had had a PIP face-to-face assessment declared that it had caused their condition to deteriorate or relapse.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","14137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425015","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-06","<p>This Government is tackling poverty through our new Life Chances agenda. This will drive real action which will make the biggest difference to the most disadvantaged children – now and in the future. This approach will ensure that Government action is focused on tackling the root causes of child poverty - worklessness, educational failure, family breakdown, problem debt and addiction.</p><p>This Government believes that work is the best route out of poverty and is therefore focused on getting people into employment. With more than two million more people in work than in 2010, and with the number of workless households at a record low, the progress made by this Government has been significant including in Barnsley Central constituency. In the constituency, over the past year, the number of people claiming Jobseeker’s Allowance, or not in work and claiming Universal Credit, fell by 13 per cent.</p><p>We do not have specific data on all former mining communities and this information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-06T14:38:50.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425015/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425015/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425015/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to reduce poverty in (a) Barnsley Central constituency and (b) other former mining communities.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","14019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425016","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>Guidance and training for Healthcare professionals advising the Department is developed by providers for their own staff. Both PIP and ESA assessments are based on function, not diagnosis or treatment.</p><p>All Jobcentre Plus work coaches are trained to have the skills required to support customers with health conditions and disabilities. They have access to information which gives specific detail around various illnesses, the effects those illnesses are likely to have and access to sites such as NHS Choices. Work coaches can also use the “Employment, Health Conditions and Disabilities” intranet guide notes which provide background on specific disabilities /conditions and advice on good practice when interviewing. Finally, via the local District Provision tool, many Work Coaches are able to signpost claimants to organisations such as Crohns and Colitis UK.</p><p>Departmental Decision Makers are given awareness of conditions, incapacities and their effects. Over time and with updates, learning and development they gather more information to increase their knowledgebase. They are also able to obtain specific advice on individual cases from Healthcare professionals employed by providers working for the Department.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-03T15:02:00.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425016/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425016/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425016/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Social Security Benefits: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that (a) health workers, (b) Jobcentre Plus staff and (c) his Department's staff have received adequate training to respond to the needs of people with Crohn's disease and Colitis, which meets the six main standards set out in the Standards for the Healthcare of People who have Inflammatory Bowel Disease, 2013 update.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","14015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425017","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>The information as requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","14048 ; 14049","2015-11-03T15:27:22.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425017/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425017/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425017/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Employment and Support Allowance: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many appeals by claimants in the work related activity group of employment and support allowance whose primary medical condition is a mental health condition have resulted in subsequent placement in the support group of employment and support allowance in each quarter since 2013.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","14055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425018","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>Jobcentre Work Coaches undertake outreach work every day in local communities, and have recently been helping people with back-to-work support and advice at the Lalley Centre in Manchester. Early feedback has been very positive. We will reflect on this and see if there is potential for extending engagement where there is local need and Jobcentre Plus are invited to do so.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","14139","2015-11-03T11:15:18.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425018/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425018/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Jobcentre Plus: Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the duration will be of the pilot project placing jobcentre advisers in food banks.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425019","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-03","<p>The available information is set out below:</p><p>(a) IT costs which can be found in the published DWP Annual Report and Accounts, are summarised as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>£ (to nearest 1,000)</p></td><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16 to September</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total IT</p></td><td><p>960,572,000</p></td><td><p>926,912,000</p></td><td><p>1,111,308,000</p></td><td><p>802,134,000</p></td><td><p>732,352,000</p></td><td><p>327,006,000*</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*Please note that the figure for 2015/16 to September has not yet been audited for accounts.</p><p>(b) DWP has tracked all core aspects of expenditure on cyber security, apart from in specific IT systems, since April 2015. The current estimate up to September 15/16 is £5.6m, with further significant investment planned for the second half of the year.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-03T17:31:56.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425019/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425019/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-29","Department for Work and Pensions: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department spent on (a) IT systems and (b) cyber-security in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13, (iv) 2013-14, (v) 2014-15 and (vi) 2015-16 to date.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","13999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424458","Attorney General","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Law Officers Departments do not hold complete records of the number of staff who are enrolled in a trade union as there is no obligation placed on a trade union to disclose this information to employers.</p><br /><p>Records are however maintained on the amount of facility time claimed during the financial year 2014/15 and the cost involved, as detailed below.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Law Officers’ Departments – Trade Union facility time and costs in 2014-15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>Facility time (hours) <sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Cost</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Government Legal Department<sup>1</sup></p></td><td><p>2,206.2</p></td><td><p>£46,302</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Serious Fraud Office</p></td><td><p>129.6</p></td><td><p>£4,069</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Crown Prosecution Service</p></td><td><p>14,267</p></td><td><p>£351,929</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><sup>1</sup> <em>The GLD data also covers the Attorney General’s Office and HM Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate.</em></p><p><sup>2 </sup><em>Only nominated trade union representatives are granted facility time.</em></p><br /><p>The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest data is Quarter 4, 2014 at and is available at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time</a> .</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-11-05T10:21:29.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424458/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424458/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-28","Attorney General: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many civil servants in the Law Officers' Departments are members of trades unions; how much working hours facility time is claimed by each such civil servant; and what the cost of that facility time is to the Law Officers' Departments.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424459","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-11","<p>There is no single data source that comprehensively measures all business start-ups within the UK.</p><p>However, ONS publishes statistics showing the number of businesses newly registered for VAT or PAYE.</p><p>These figures are available from the ONS Business Demography releases.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-11T14:54:40.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424459/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424459/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","New Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of how many small businesses have been started in (a) Bristol, (b) London and (c) England in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","13933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424460","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>This Department is regularly in contact with the Ministry of Defence (MoD) about the impact of industrial issues on the UK defence industry and supply chain, such as the challenges facing the steel industry. Any implications for defence procurement will also be considered by the steel procurement working group which was set up with cross-departmental representation (including MoD) following the Steel Summit.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-09T14:54:42.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424460/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424460/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Defence Equipment: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions his Department has had with the Ministry of Defence on the potential implications of the closure of steel plants in the UK for the UK defence industry and infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","13939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424461","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-02","<p>Estimates of the impact of freezing the repayment thresholds for borrowers are illustrated in the consultation document, which has been published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/freezing-the-student-loan-repayment-threshold" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/freezing-the-student-loan-repayment-threshold</a></p><p>These are based on analysis using the Department’s Student Loan Repayment Model: further details on the model are available at the Department’s website <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/simplified-student-loan-repayment-model" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/simplified-student-loan-repayment-model</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-02T11:06:55.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424461/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424461/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the evidential basis is for the proposition that freezing the repayment threshold for plan 2 student loans is likely to result in student loans being repaid to a greater extent than under the current terms.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","13854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424462","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-02","<p>The assessment of additional loan repayments has been set out in the published consultation document which is published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/freezing-the-student-loan-repayment-threshold" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/freezing-the-student-loan-repayment-threshold</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-02T11:06:05.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424462/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424462/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effects of the Government's proposal to freeze the repayment threshold for plan 2 student loans on the amount of money likely to be paid back over the 30 year repayment period.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","13855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424463","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Department does not hold information on how many civil servants are members of Trade Unions. The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest data is Quarter 4, 2014 at and is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time</a>.</p><p>The Department collects this information on a quarterly basis. The last period for which we have data is Quarter 2 of 2015, 1 April – 30 June 2015. During this period, the 33 TU reps claimed a total of 913 hours of facility time at a cost of £18,933.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-09T15:03:36.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424463/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424463/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil servants in his Department are members of trades unions; how much working hours facility time is claimed by each such civil servant; and what the cost of that facility time is to his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424464","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>From 1 April 2015, the ACAS Helpline is, in addition to its usual services, answering queries previously handled by the Pay and Work rights Helpline. This provides a one stop shop for those seeking advice and guidance on employment rights. Where appropriate, ACAS passes on callers through a real time transfer of the call to the relevant enforcement body for them to take any further follow up action, including any specific complaints.</p><p>No formal assessment has been made at this time of the outcomes for workers. ACAS continues to work closely with the four enforcement bodies to ensure the service is bedding in effectively and delivering the right outcomes for the public.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-09T15:08:25.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424464/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424464/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","ACAS: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment has been made of the effect of incorporating the function of the Pay and Work Rights Helpline into ACAS on outcomes for workers.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","13746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424465","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-04","<p>There are no plans to ban support for exports of goods and services to coal plants and coal mining overseas. However, applications to UK Export Finance (UKEF) which fall within the ambit of the OECD Common Approaches for Officially Supported Export Credits and Environmental and Social Due Diligence will require that coal projects meet international, environmental, social, and human rights standards to qualify for support. <br> <br> UKEF is participating in discussions in the OECD with the aim of achieving a multilateral agreement on limiting the provision of export credits for coal-fired power projects and an agreement is expected to be reached later in November.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-04T11:39:59.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424465/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424465/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","UK Export Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will make it his policy to eliminate UK Export Finance investments in coal plants and coal mining overseas.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","13744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424466","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-18","<p>The Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills has no plans to hold such a meeting.</p><p>It is illegal to reduce the mileage on a car and advertise or sell it on that basis. This is the case regardless of the availability of devices that can reduce vehicle mileage. For advice on alleged offences of misleading advertising or fraud, consumers should approach Action Fraud or Citizens Advice, who may refer cases to Trading Standards.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-18T12:46:14.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424466/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424466/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Motor Vehicles: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will hold discussions with motor trade associations on steps to ban the sale of devices that are used to illegally reduce car mileages on vehicles for resale.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","13758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424467","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-02","<br /><p>While information is already shared between labour market enforcement bodies, the existing information sharing gateways in numerous Acts of Parliament are limited as regards with whom information can be shared and for what purpose. Legislative changes may be required to allow greater information sharing between enforcement bodies. For example we want to ensure that HMRC National Minimum Wage enforcement officers are able to share information effectively with the Health and Safety Executive and local authorities.</p><br /><p>We are also engaging with the relevant enforcement bodies to identify possible non-legislative barriers to information sharing.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-02T17:07:51.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424467/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424467/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-28","Employment: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to paragraph 62 of the Government's consultation document, Tackling Exploitation in the Labour Market, published in October 2015, what limitations currently exist on data sharing between labour market enforcement bodies.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","13810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424468","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) already extends to over 100,000 public authorities. We constantly keep the list of bodies covered by the FOIA under review.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-16T11:11:30.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424468/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424468/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424468/answer/previousversion/27239","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will bring forward proposals to add the (a) Surveillance Camera Commissioner and (b) Office of the Biometrics Commissioner to Schedule 1 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","13811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424469","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>This information is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-02T17:20:58.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424469/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424469/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Senior Civil Servants: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the cost of using external agencies for recruitment to the Senior Civil Service across all Government departments in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424470","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>There are no indications of a cyber security breach of the Government Gateway.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-05T17:50:23.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424470/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424470/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Electronic Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will contact those people whose personal details have been stolen as a result of the cyber security breach of the Government Gateway system.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424471","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>The Government takes cyber security very seriously.We have invested more than £860 million in cyber-security and we will continue to do everything in our power to protect organisations and individuals from attacks.Government Gateway has an on-going security programme, and more broadlyCyber security is a Tier 1 risk in the National Strategic Risk Assessment, alongside international terrorism. We urge all online service users to keep their log-in details safe, be suspicious of unsolicited emails and keep their anti-virus software up to date.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-02T17:53:24.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424471/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424471/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Electronic Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to ensure that personal information housed on the Government Gateway system is better protected.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424472","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>On 30 June 2014, the Electoral Office for Northern Ireland had (a) 19,361 18 year olds and (b) 20,746 19 year olds registered to vote. Drawing on the mid-year population estimate for 2014 published by the Office for National Statistics, this would represent 82.8% of 18-19 year olds in Northern Ireland.</p><p>The Electoral Commission last assessed the completeness of the Northern Ireland electoral register in 2012 when survey sampling estimated that 51% of 18-19 year olds were registered to vote. An Electoral Commission report on the quality of the 2014 electoral registers in Great Britain assessed that 76% of 18-19 year olds were registered to vote.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has not made a separate assessment of the number of 18 and 19 year olds registered in either Great Britain or Northern Ireland in this period.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-11-05T13:07:45.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424472/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424472/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-10-28","Electoral Register: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many and what proportion of (a) 18 and (b) 19 year-olds in Northern Ireland were registered to vote on 30 June 2014; what the average number was of 18 and 19 year-olds in Northern Ireland so registered as a proportion of the mid-year population estimate made by the Office for National Statistics for 2014; and how that figure differs from (i) Electoral Commission and (ii) Cabinet Office estimates of the number of registered 18 and 19 year-olds in (A) Northern Ireland and (B) Great Britain in 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","13739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424473","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>It is for the independent Commission on Freedom of Information to organise its programme of work.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-04T10:05:56.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424473/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424473/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Commission on Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions he has had with the Independent Commission the Freedom of Information on the number of occasions it plans to meet in order to finalise its report.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424475","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-11-04T10:03:33.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424475/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424475/answer","PQ 13823 Nicholas Brown MP.pdf","PQ 13823 Nicholas Brown MP.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Migration Figures","UKSA Letter to Member - Migration Figures","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424475/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Office for National Statistics plans to include in quarterly migration figures the number of Syrian refugees resettled in the UK under the Government's relocation scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","13823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424476","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>We are finalising the data for government spend with small business during 2014-15 and will publish this information before the end of the year.</p><p>Data for 2015-16 will be published in due course.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-05T17:42:53.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424476/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424476/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Government Departments: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of government IT spending was spent with small and medium sized (SME) enterprises in 2014-15; and what estimate  he has made of the proportion of that spending that will be with SMEs in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424477","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>To date the security reports on the Government Gateway system have shown no indication of a cyber security breach. We are continuously monitoring and managing the security risks to all HMG systems,taking appropriate action where necessary and ensuring we maintain the best possible level of security.</p><p>We are aware Government Gateway credentials stored outside government systems have been harvested by malware. This highlights the importance of users implementing and maintaining good security practices, for example, installing and updating anti-virus software, as well as never sharing or using a single password for all internet activities.</p><p>We will continue to increase our levels of security monitoring and management on all our systems.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-02T17:21:38.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424477/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424477/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Electronic Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of (a) which personal details and (b) how many individual profiles were hacked as a result of the cyber security breach of the Government Gateway system.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424478","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-02","<p>This is an operational matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), who are operationally independent from Government. The question has been passed on to the FCA. The FCA will reply to you directly by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","13913","2015-11-02T15:13:33.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424478/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424478/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Financial Services: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many registered financial advisers are sole traders.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","13942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424479","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-05","<p>The analysis that fed into the published Impact Assessment<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> shows how the £4.4bn of savings from the tax credit changes as laid out in the publication are distributed for each income decile on the income distribution for tax credit claimants. This has clearly demonstrated that tax credit claimants on the highest incomes – on average £42,000 a year - will contribute nearly 4 times as much as the claimants on the lowest incomes to the savings from this policy.</p><p>This Government is committed to moving from a high welfare, high tax, low wage economy to a lower welfare, lower tax, higher wage society. As the Chancellor has made clear, the Government will set out at Autumn Statement how we plan to achieve the same goal of reforming tax credits, saving the money we need to save to secure our economy, while at the same time helping in the transition.</p><p>[1] http://www.parliament.uk/documents/lords-committees/Secondary-Legislation-Scrutiny-Committee/DraftTaxCreditsRegs2015-ImpactAssessment.pdf</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-11-05T15:50:33.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424479/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424479/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to his Department's impact assessment on the Tax Credits (Income Threshold and Determination of Rates) (Amendment) Regulations 2015, what the (a) income brackets are for each decile and (b) equivalent levels are for the proportions in Chart 1.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","13929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424481","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-06","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not track each customer journey end to end through the phone system, and cannot therefore provide the average duration time as requested.</p><br /><p>HMRC does not hold information of the cost of a call to its lines. I would refer to my answer given on 13 July 2015 to UIN 5712.</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-06T12:31:53.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424481/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424481/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Welfare Tax Credits: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average (a) duration and (b) cost to the caller of a telephone call to HM Revenue and Customs' tax credit telephone lines was in the most recent 12 months for which data is available; and how much revenue was generated from these calls.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","13966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424482","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-06","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not hold this information.</p><br /><p>HMRC has a number of significant peaks of customer contact every year, and since 2005 it has moved its resources around to meet those seasonal priorities.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-06T12:40:53.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424482/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424482/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Welfare Tax Credits: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many staff have been employed to cover HM Revenue and Customs' tax credit telephone lines in each of the past five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","13967"
